'''Yractos''' was the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[City/Legends|city]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Gyndine/Legends|Gyndine]]. It was among the largest of the world's settlements.

In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], the city was host to a slaving ring scandal.

During the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], Yractos was [[Battle of Gyndine|savaged]] by a Yuuzhan Vong assault force, which leveled much of its skyline and urban area with yorik coral missiles. The area was sacked by [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Warrior caste|warriors]] and [[Chazrach]] soldiers, further destroying Yractos's infrastructure. Following the assault, [[Refugee/Legends|refugees]] from various conquered worlds, formerly under [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo's]] efforts to evacuate them to [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] space, were coralled into isolation areas and shipped offworld. The city would remain under the [[Yuuzhan Vong empire]]'s control for the duration of the war.

==Behind the scenes==
Yractos made its first appearance in the New Jedi Order novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Agents of Chaos II: Jedi Eclipse]]'', during the battle there. However, despite the prolific events taking place in the city, Yractos was never mentioned by name.

